 guy=3F =E2=80=A6 who =E2=80=9Carrived in Puerto Rico seven years ago, prom=
ising to =0Ause crypto magic to revitalize the local economy=E2=80=9D and t=
hen mostly did hijinks:=0A=0AFor a while, Mr. Pierce managed to charm some =
of the locals with his openness =0Aand curiosity. He had the chameleonic in=
stincts of a skilled actor, adjusting =0Ahis behavior to suit the audience.=
 =E2=80=9CIf it was serious people, he=E2=80=99d act =0Aseriously,=E2=80=9D=
 said Hugo de la Uz, a local maritime expert who helped manage Mr. =0APierc=
e=E2=80=99s yacht. =E2=80=9CIf it was crazy people, he=E2=80=99d act crazy.=
=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6=0A=0ASince he moved to Puerto Rico, Mr. Pierce has boug=
ht at least 14 properties, =0Aaccording to real estate records. Some, like =
the Monastery, were already =0Afunctioning businesses. But Mr. Pierce also =
announced plans to convert much of =0Ahis portfolio into new projects, incl=
uding an art gallery and a community =0Acenter. None of those ventures has =
come to fruition. A hospital in the city of =0AHumacao that he bought late =
last year has struggled, and the gallery was =0Arecently listed for sale. I=
n 2019, Mr. Pierce took over a three-story building =0Athat once housed a c=
hildren=E2=80=99s museum in Old San Juan; for a while, he told the =0Alocal=
 media, he used it as =E2=80=9Ca space to meet and discuss big ideas.=E2=80=
=9D Today, the =0Abuilding is empty, paint peeling from its walls.=0A=0AThe=
re=E2=80=99s an alleged kidnapping of a business partner:=0A=0AIn court, Mr=
. Pierce has denied misusing the borrowed money or kidnapping Mr. =0ALipse=
y. But when the W dispute began, he wasn=E2=80=99t in a healthy frame of mi=
nd, =0Asaid one of his advisers, Cassandra Wesselman, who recently moved to=
 Puerto =0ARico. Ms. Wesselman said it was she who had suggested bringing t=
he armed guard =0Ato the Hacienda Tamarindo =E2=80=94 to protect Mr. Pierce=
 from a couple who were =0Astaying in another room. They belonged to a cult=
, she explained, and she =0Abelieved that they had been exercising a malign=
 influence over Mr. Pierce. (In =0Aresponse, Mr. Pierce called that account=
