d keep some of it for yourself.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Etc.=
</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The people who get into the scheme e=
arly and recruit a lot of new members (who recruit a lot of new members, et=
c., recursively) can actually make a lot of money, all of it from the later=
 members; the people who get in late are suckers. Occasionally people do th=
is literally and with their eyes open, but (1) it=E2=80=99s generally illeg=
al and (2) it is somewhat evidently=C2=A0<em>bad=C2=A0</em>(you should not =
get in late!), so most pyramid schemes are embedded in other =E2=80=9Cmulti=
level marketing=E2=80=9D businesses. The idea there is:</p><ol style=3D"lis=
t-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"> <li style=3D"m=
argin-bottom: 5px;">You recruit some members to invest some money.</li> <li=
 style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">That money goes to buy the=C2=A0product, whi=
ch the members are supposed to sell.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>Those members also recruit new members to invest more money.</li> <li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some of that money goes to buy a product, but som=
e of it goes to the Step 1=C2=A0members who recruited them.</li> <li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Etc.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If ever=
yone in the pyramid makes money=C2=A0<em>mostly=C2=A0</em>by selling produc=
